<p><b>Airbnb, Inc.</b> (<span class=3D"rt-commentedText nowrap"><span class=
=3D"IPA nopopups noexcerpt" lang=3D"en-fonipa"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Help:IPA/English" title=3D"Help:IPA/English">/<span style=3D"b=
order-bottom:1px dotted"><span title=3D"/=CB=8C/: secondary stress follows"=
>=CB=8C</span><span title=3D"/=C9=9B=C9=99r/: 'are' in 'bare'">=C9=9B=C9=99=
r</span><span title=3D"'b' in 'buy'">b</span><span title=3D"/i=CB=90/: 'ee'=
 in 'fleece'">i=CB=90</span><span title=3D"/=C9=9B/: 'e' in 'dress'">=C9=9B=
</span><span title=3D"'n' in 'nigh'">n</span><span title=3D"/=CB=88/: prima=
ry stress follows">=CB=88</span><span title=3D"'b' in 'buy'">b</span><span =
title=3D"/i=CB=90/: 'ee' in 'fleece'">i=CB=90</span></span>/</a></span></sp=
an> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Pronunciation_respelling_=
key" title=3D"Help:Pronunciation respelling key"><i title=3D"English pronun=
ciation respelling"><span style=3D"font-size:90%">AIR</span>-bee-en-<span s=
tyle=3D"font-size:90%">BEE</span></i></a>, an abbreviation of its original =
name, "<b>Air Bed and Breakfast</b>"<sup id=3D"cite_ref-5" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-5"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
) is an American company operating  an online marketplace for short-and-lon=
g-term <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homestay" title=3D"Homestay=
">homestays</a>, experiences and services in various countries and regions.=
 It acts as a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Broker" title=3D"Bro=
ker">broker</a> and charges a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comm=
ission_(remuneration)" title=3D"Commission (remuneration)">commission</a> f=
rom each booking. Airbnb was founded in 2008 by <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Brian_Chesky" title=3D"Brian Chesky">Brian Chesky</a>, <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nathan_Blecharczyk" title=3D"Nathan Blec=
harczyk">Nathan Blecharczyk</a>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Joe_Gebbia" title=3D"Joe Gebbia">Joe Gebbia</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-6" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_not=
e-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"toclimit-3"><meta property=3D"mw:PageProp/toc"></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"History">History</h2><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAirbnb&amp;action=3Ded=
it&amp;section=3D1" title=3D"Edit section: History"><span>edit</span></a><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>After moving to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Francisco" =
title=3D"San Francisco">San Francisco</a> in October 2007, roommates and fo=
rmer schoolmates <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brian_Chesky" tit=
le=3D"Brian Chesky">Brian Chesky</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Joe_Gebbia" title=3D"Joe Gebbia">Joe Gebbia</a> came up with an idea=
 of putting an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_mattress" title=
=3D"Air mattress">air mattress</a> in their living room and turning it into=
 a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bed_and_breakfast" title=3D"Bed=
 and breakfast">bed and breakfast</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-howair_8-0" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-ho=
wair-8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup> In February 2008, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Nathan_Blecharczyk" title=3D"Nathan Blecharczyk">Nathan Blecharczyk</a>,=
 Chesky's former roommate, joined as the chief technology officer and the t=
hird co-founder of the new venture, which they named "AirBed &amp; Breakfas=
t".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-howair_8-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-howair-8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_r=
ef-9" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#c=
ite_note-9"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">]</span></a></sup> They put together a website that offered short-term =
living quarters and breakfast for those who were unable to book a hotel in =
the saturated market.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-howair_8-2" class=3D"reference"><a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-howair-8"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> The site Airbedandbreakfast.com was launched on August 11, 2008.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-10" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Airbnb#cite_note-10"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>10<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-11"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up> The founders had their first customers in the summer of 2008, during th=
e Industrial Design Conference held by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Industrial_Designers_Society_of_America" title=3D"Industrial Designers=
 Society of America">Industrial Designers Society of America</a>, where tra=
velers had a hard time finding lodging in the city.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-12" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_no=
te-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>After the founders raised $30,000 by selling cereal named after the =
two candidates of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2008_United_=
States_presidential_election" title=3D"2008 United States presidential elec=
tion">2008 United States presidential election</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Barack_Obama" title=3D"Barack Obama">Barack Obama</a> and=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_McCain" title=3D"John McCain=
">John McCain</a>, mostly at the 2008 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Democratic_National_Convention" title=3D"Democratic National Convention=
">Democratic National Convention</a>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-13" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-13"><span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></=
sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-14" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-14"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-cash_15-0=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_=
note-cash-15"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">]</span></a></sup> computer programmer <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Paul_Graham_(computer_programmer)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Paul Graham (computer programmer)">Paul Graham</a> invited the founders=
 to the January 2009 winter training session of his startup incubator, <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Y_Combinator_(company)" class=3D"mw-re=
direct" title=3D"Y Combinator (company)">Y Combinator</a>, which provided t=
hem with training and $20,000 in funding in exchange for a 6% interest in t=
he company.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-howair_8-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-howair-8"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-112million_16-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-112million-16"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-17" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb=
#cite_note-17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup> With the website already built, they used the Y =
Combinator investment to fly to New York to meet users and promote the site=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-cash_15-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-cash-15"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> They returned to Sa=
n Francisco with a profitable business model to present to West Coast inves=
tors. By March 2009, the site had 10,000 users and 2,500 listings.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-ycombinator_18-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-ycombinator-18"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>18<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In March 2009, the name of the company was shortened to Airbnb.com t=
o eliminate confusion over air mattresses.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-howair_8-4" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_not=
e-howair-8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">]</span></a></sup> At the March 2011 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/South_by_Southwest" title=3D"South by Southwest">South by Southwest<=
/a> conference, Airbnb won the "app" award.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-19" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-19"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>19<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup> In July 2014, Airbnb revealed design revisions to the site and m=
obile app and introduced a new logo.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-20" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-20"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>20<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up><sup id=3D"cite_ref-21" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-21"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>21<s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> It also announced a partnersh=
ip with Concur, an expense reporting service for businesses.<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-22" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbn=
b#cite_note-22"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In April 2015, following the easing of restrictions on U.S. business=
es to operate in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cuba" title=3D"Cu=
ba">Cuba</a>, Airbnb expanded to Cuba, making it one of the first U.S. comp=
anies to do so.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-23" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-23"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
[</span>23<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-24" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#c=
ite_note-24"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>24<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup> In July 2016, former Attorney General <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eric_Holder" title=3D"Eric Holder">Eric Holder=
</a> was hired to help craft an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/An=
ti-discrimination_law" title=3D"Anti-discrimination law">anti-discriminatio=
n policy</a> for Airbnb after reports showed that hosts were refusing to ac=
cept lodging requests from guests whose names suggested that they were blac=
k.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-25" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-25"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>25<sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> As part of the reform, photos =
of prospective guests are hidden from hosts until requests for lodging are =
accepted.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-26" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-26"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</spa=
n>26<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In November 2016, Airbnb launched "experiences", whereby users can u=
se the platform to book activities.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-27" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-27"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>27<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p> In January 2017, along with serial entrepreneurs <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Gary_Vaynerchuk" title=3D"Gary Vaynerchuk">Gary Vaynerchu=
k</a>, Ben Leventhal and Mike Montero, Airbnb led a $13 million investment =
in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resy" title=3D"Resy">Resy</a>, =
a restaurant reservation-booking app.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-28" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-28"><span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>28<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></=
sup> In May 2017, the company launched Airbnbmag, a magazine co-published w=
ith <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hearst_Communications" title=
=3D"Hearst Communications">Hearst Communications</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-29=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_=
note-29"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>29<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In February 2018, the company announced Airbnb Plus, a collection of=
 homes vetted for quality of services, comfort and design,<sup id=3D"cite_r=
ef-30" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#=
cite_note-30"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>30<span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">]</span></a></sup> as well as Beyond by Airbnb, which offers luxury =
vacation rentals.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-31" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-31"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>31<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> By October 2019=
, two million people were staying with Airbnb each night.<sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-32" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#c=
ite_note-32"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>32<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup> In April 2019, Airbnb produced and financed <i><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gay_Chorus_Deep_South" title=3D"Gay C=
horus Deep South">Gay Chorus Deep South</a></i>, a documentary launched by =
its Rausch Street Films division. The rights were sold to <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MTV" title=3D"MTV">MTV</a>, which aired the program=
 on its network.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-33" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-33"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>33<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_r=
ef-34" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#=
cite_note-34"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>34<span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-35" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-35"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>35<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>During the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/COVID-19_pandemi=
c" title=3D"COVID-19 pandemic">COVID-19 pandemic</a>, bookings dropped as m=
uch as 96% in some cities.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-36" class=3D"reference"><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-36"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>36<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Howeve=
r, bookings rose in many rural areas.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-37" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-37"><span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>37<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></=
sup> The company pledged $250 million in payouts to hosts to compensate the=
m for guest cancellations due to the pandemic.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-38" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-38=
"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>38<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-39" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-39"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>39<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The company also <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Layoff" title=3D"Layoff">laid off</a=
> approximately 1,900 employees, or about 25% of its workforce in the Ameri=
cas, Europe, and Asia due to the pandemic.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-40" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-40"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>40<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span><=
/a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-41" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-41"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</spa=
n>41<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> On December 10, 2020, A=
irbnb (ticker symbol: "ABNB") became a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Public_company" title=3D"Public company">public company</a> via an <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Initial_public_offering" title=3D"Ini=
tial public offering">initial public offering</a>, raising $3.5 billion on =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nasdaq" title=3D"Nasdaq">Nasdaq</a=
>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-42" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-42"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>42<sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Shares valued at $238 million =
were offered to hosts on the platform at the price of $68 per share.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-43" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Airbnb#cite_note-43"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>43<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In March 2022, Airbnb suspended business in <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Russia" title=3D"Russia">Russia</a> and <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belarus" title=3D"Belarus">Belarus</a> due to the sa=
nctions resulting from the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian=
_invasion_of_Ukraine" title=3D"Russian invasion of Ukraine">Russian invasio=
n of Ukraine</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-44" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-44"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>44<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-45" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb=
#cite_note-45"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>45<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup> In May 2022, Airbnb ceased operations in <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China" title=3D"China">China</a>.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-46" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Airbnb#cite_note-46"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>46<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The decision was made primarily becaus=
e of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_government_response_t=
o_COVID-19#Zero-COVID_policy" title=3D"Chinese government response to COVID=
-19">China's Zero-COVID policy</a>, as well as complicated and expensive la=
ws and regulations that required Airbnb to send detailed information on gue=
sts to the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_China" ti=
tle=3D"Government of China">government of China</a>, which can be used to t=
rack people.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-47" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-47"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</=
span>47<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-4=
8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite=
_note-48"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>48<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-49" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-49"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>49<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Airbnb was accused of being too willing to provide this information,=
 which led to the resignation of an Airbnb executive, who was also a former=
 deputy director of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Federal_Bu=
reau_of_Investigation" title=3D"Federal Bureau of Investigation">Federal Bu=
reau of Investigation</a>, in 2019 after 6 months of working.<sup id=3D"cit=
e_ref-50" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airb=
nb#cite_note-50"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>50<span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-51" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-51"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>51<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Airb=
nb had also been accused of allowing listings on land owned by the <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xinjiang_Production_and_Construction_Corp=
s" title=3D"Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps">Xinjiang Production=
 and Construction Corps</a>, a Chinese state-owned paramilitary entity sanc=
tioned under the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnitsky_Act" ti=
tle=3D"Magnitsky Act">Magnitsky Act</a> for involvement in the <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persecution_of_Uyghurs_in_China" title=3D"Pers=
ecution of Uyghurs in China">persecution of Uyghurs in China</a>.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-52" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Airbnb#cite_note-52"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>52<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-53" class=3D"reference"=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-53"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>53<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
 In 2019, certain hosts in China were accused of discrimination by refusing=
 to rent to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uyghurs" title=3D"Uygh=
urs">Uyghurs</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-54" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-54"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>54<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>After temporarily banning parties in homes rented on the platform in=
 August 2020 due to the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/COVID-19_p=
andemic" title=3D"COVID-19 pandemic">COVID-19 pandemic</a>,<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-55" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb=
#cite_note-55"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>55<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup> in June 2022, Airbnb announced that it would per=
manently ban parties and events in homes on its platform, a position suppor=
ted by hosts and their neighbors who complained of nuisances at Airbnb prop=
erties.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-56" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-56"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
56<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In August 2022, Airbnb ro=
lled out technology to enforce this ban.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-57" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-57"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>57<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup>
</p><p>In June 2025, Airbnb became a commercial partner for the <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FIFA_Club_World_Cup" title=3D"FIFA Club World=
 Cup">FIFA Club World Cup</a>. As part of this, they offered official fan a=
ccommodation as part of a three-year deal with Fifa that also includes the =
2026 men=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FIFA_World_Cup"=
 title=3D"FIFA World Cup">World Cup</a>, which the US is co-hosting with Ca=
nada and Mexico, and the 2027 Women=E2=80=99s World Cup in Brazil.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-58" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Airbnb#cite_note-58"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>58<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
