<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Criticism_and_controversies=
">Criticism and controversies</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span clas=
s=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/=
index.php?title=3DAirbnb&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D10" title=3D"Edit =
section: Criticism and controversies"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"m=
w-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The company has been criticized for possibly enabling increases in home =
rents,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-164" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-164"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>164<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> refusing to provide sen=
sitive customer data to governments, and allowing listings in <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Bank_settlement" class=3D"mw-redirect" tit=
le=3D"West Bank settlement">West Bank settlements</a>. Airbnb has been crit=
icized by the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel_industry" clas=
s=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Hotel industry">hotel industry</a> for not being=
 subject to fair regulations.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-165" class=3D"reference"><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-165"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>165<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> Critics have also noted how Airbnb resists sharing its listing data with =
regulators, often citing privacy protections as its reason for not cooperat=
ing.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-166" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-166"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1=
66<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Effects_on_housing_affordab=
ility">Effects on housing affordability</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection">=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAirbnb&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" titl=
e=3D"Edit section: Effects on housing affordability"><span>edit</span></a><=
span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Several studies have found that short-term rental has contributed to the=
 increase of long-term rental prices due to changes in housing <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supply_and_demand" title=3D"Supply and demand"=
>supply and demand</a>. Landlords have kept properties off the longer-term =
rental market to instead get higher rental rates for short-term housing via=
 Airbnb.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-167" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-167"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>167<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-16=
8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite=
_note-168"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>168<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-169" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-169"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>169<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-170" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Airbnb#cite_note-170"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>170<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-171" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-171"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>171<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-ODD23_110-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-ODD23-110"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>110<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-172" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Airbnb#cite_note-172"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>172<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-173" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-173"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>173<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inside_Airbnb" title=3D"I=
nside Airbnb">Inside Airbnb</a>, a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Watchdog_journalism" title=3D"Watchdog journalism">watchdog journalism</a>=
 website, has accused the company of manipulating its data to portray a dif=
ferent result.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-174" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-174"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>174<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Landlords have =
also been accused of illegally <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evi=
ct" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Evict">evicting</a> tenants to convert p=
roperties into higher-rent Airbnb listings.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-175" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-17=
5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>175<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup> Concerns on the effect of Airbnb on <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Affordable_housing" title=3D"Affordable housing">housing =
affordability</a> has resulted in increased <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Lodging#Regulation_of_commercial_lodging" title=3D"Lodging">lodgi=
ng regulations</a> and restrictions, which have generally been opposed by A=
irbnb via <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lobbying" title=3D"Lobby=
ing">lobbying</a> efforts.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-176" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-176"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>176<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Thi=
s phenomenon has been dubbed the "Airbnb effect".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-177" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_not=
e-177"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>177<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Inclusion_of_listings_in_Is=
raeli_settlements">Inclusion of listings in Israeli settlements</h3><span c=
lass=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAirbnb&amp;action=3Dedi=
t&amp;section=3D12" title=3D"Edit section: Inclusion of listings in Israeli=
 settlements"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]=
</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
See also: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_companies_operat=
ing_in_West_Bank_settlements" title=3D"List of companies operating in West =
Bank settlements">List of companies operating in West Bank settlements</a><=
/div>
<p>In November 2018, Airbnb announced that it would remove the approximatel=
y 200 "listings in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israeli_settlem=
ents" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Israeli settlements">Israeli settlemen=
ts</a> in the occupied <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Bank" =
title=3D"West Bank">West Bank</a> that are at the core of the dispute betwe=
en Israelis and Palestinians". However, after affected property owners file=
d lawsuits against Airbnb in both Israel and the United States alleging dis=
crimination based on place of residence, in April 2019, the company reverse=
d its plans to remove listings in the West Bank and instead promised to don=
ate any profits from these listings to non-profit organizations dedicated t=
o <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Humanitarian_aid" title=3D"Human=
itarian aid">humanitarian aid</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-178" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-178"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>178<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></=
sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-179" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-179"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1=
79<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-180" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_not=
e-180"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>180<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>On February 12, 2020, Airbnb was included on a <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_companies_operating_in_West_Bank_settlements" t=
itle=3D"List of companies operating in West Bank settlements">list of compa=
nies operating in West Bank settlements</a> involved in activities that "ra=
ised particular human rights concerns" published by the <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Nations_Human_Rights_Council" title=3D"United =
Nations Human Rights Council">United Nations Human Rights Council</a>. The =
company was categorized under "the provision of services and utilities supp=
orting the maintenance and existence of settlements".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-18=
1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite=
_note-181"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>181<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-182" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-182"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>182<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Criticism_by_the_hotel_indu=
stry">Criticism by the hotel industry</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/w/index.php?title=3DAirbnb&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D13" title=
=3D"Edit section: Criticism by the hotel industry"><span>edit</span></a><sp=
an class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Airbnb has been criticized by the hotel industry due to its competitive =
effects and its different regulations. This has led to a decline in hotel r=
evenue in some markets and an increase in lobbying by the hotel industry.<s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-183" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-183"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>183<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-184" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-18=
4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>184<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-185" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-185"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>185<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Lack_of_loyalty_program">La=
ck of loyalty program</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-=
editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.ph=
p?title=3DAirbnb&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D14" title=3D"Edit section:=
 Lack of loyalty program"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Airbnb is one of the few major travel companies without a loyalty progra=
m, which has led to criticism by many customers. This is in part attributed=
 to its lack of business customers, as reported by <i><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Wall_Street_Journal" title=3D"The Wall Street Journ=
al">The Wall Street Journal</a></i>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-186" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-186"><span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>186<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a>=
</sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Objectivity_of_guest_review=
s">Objectivity of guest reviews</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span cl=
ass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
w/index.php?title=3DAirbnb&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D15" title=3D"Edi=
t section: Objectivity of guest reviews"><span>edit</span></a><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Airbnb features a review system in which guests and hosts can rate and r=
eview each other after a stay. Hosts and guests are unable to see reviews u=
ntil both have submitted a review or until the time period to review has cl=
osed, a system that aims to improve accuracy and objectivity by removing fe=
ars that users will receive a negative review in retaliation if they write =
one. However, the truthfulness and impartiality of reviews may be adversely=
 affected by concerns of future stays because prospective hosts may refuse =
to host a user who generally leaves negative reviews. The company's policy =
requires users to forego anonymity, which may also detract from users' will=
ingness to leave negative reviews. These factors may damage the objectivity=
 of the review system.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-187" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-187"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>187<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-188" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Airbnb#cite_note-188"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>188<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-189" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-189"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>189<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Joe_Gebbia's_work_for_DOGE"=
><span id=3D"Joe_Gebbia.27s_work_for_DOGE"></span>Joe Gebbia's work for DOG=
E</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAirbnb&amp=
;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D16" title=3D"Edit section: Joe Gebbia's work f=
or DOGE"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</spa=
n></span></div>
<p>In February 2025, Airbnb cofounder and board member <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joe_Gebbia" title=3D"Joe Gebbia">Joe Gebbia</a> joined=
 the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Department_of_Government_Effi=
ciency" title=3D"Department of Government Efficiency">Department of Governm=
ent Efficiency</a> (DOGE).<sup id=3D"cite_ref-190" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-190"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>190<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Con=
cern that Gebbia's work for DOGE undermines U.S. democracy resulted in wide=
spread calls to boycott Airbnb.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-191" class=3D"reference"=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-191"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>191<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Response_to_activities_of_f=
ar-right_extremists">Response to activities of far-right extremists</h3><sp=
an class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span>=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAirbnb&amp;action=
=3Dedit&amp;section=3D17" title=3D"Edit section: Response to activities of =
far-right extremists"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-br=
acket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In August 2017, Airbnb cancelled numerous bookings and closed accounts b=
elonging to attendees of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/White=
_supremacist" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"White supremacist">white supre=
macist</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unite_the_Right_rally" =
title=3D"Unite the Right rally">Unite the Right rally</a> in <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charlottesville,_Virginia" title=3D"Charlottesvi=
lle, Virginia">Charlottesville, Virginia</a>, citing its <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terms_of_service" title=3D"Terms of service">terms o=
f service</a> in which members must "accept people regardless of their race=
, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Religion" title=3D"Religion">rel=
igion</a>, national origin, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethnic=
_group" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Ethnic group">ethnicity</a>, <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disability" title=3D"Disability">disabili=
ty</a>, sex, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gender_identity" titl=
e=3D"Gender identity">gender identity</a>, sexual orientation, or age."<sup=
 id=3D"cite_ref-192" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-192"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>192<span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The move was criticized by <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jason_Kessler" title=3D"Jason Kessler">J=
ason Kessler</a>, organizer of the rally.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-193" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-193"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>193<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup>
</p><p>In January 2021, Airbnb was criticized for allowing participants in =
the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/January_6_United_States_Capito=
l_attack" title=3D"January 6 United States Capitol attack">January 6 attack=
 on the United States Capitol</a> to book units on the platform in the <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Washington_metropolitan_area" title=3D=
"Washington metropolitan area">Washington metropolitan area</a>, despite mo=
st hotels in the vicinity of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capit=
ol_Hill" title=3D"Capitol Hill">Capitol Hill</a> banning <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Far-right_extremist" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"=
Far-right extremist">far-right extremists</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-194" clas=
s=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-1=
94"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>194<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup> After the possibility of further violence during the <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inauguration_of_Joe_Biden" title=3D"Ina=
uguration of Joe Biden">Inauguration of Joe Biden</a>, Airbnb announced the=
 day after the Capitol raid that it was banning all bookings in the region =
prior to the inauguration.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-195" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-195"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>195<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In 2023, Airbnb was criticized by conservative media for removing th=
e parents of Canadian <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Far-right" c=
lass=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Far-right">far-right</a> activist <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lauren_Southern" title=3D"Lauren Southern">La=
uren Southern</a> from its platform. Airbnb quickly reversed its decision, =
saying it had been a "mistake".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-whistleblower_196-0" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-=
whistleblower-196"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>196<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In May 2024, a former Airbnb contractor alleged in a <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whistleblower" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Whi=
stleblower">whistleblower</a> complaint that the company had weakened its p=
olicies against extremists and dissolved its team for removing them. Airbnb=
 denied the allegations.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-197" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-197"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>197<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup i=
d=3D"cite_ref-whistleblower_196-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-whistleblower-196"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>196<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Sponsorship_of_2022_Winter_=
Olympics">Sponsorship of 2022 Winter Olympics</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsec=
tion"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAirbnb&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D18=
" title=3D"Edit section: Sponsorship of 2022 Winter Olympics"><span>edit</s=
pan></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Airbnb was one of the 15 leading sponsors of the <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/2022_Winter_Olympics" title=3D"2022 Winter Olympics">2022=
 Winter Olympics</a>, held in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beij=
ing" title=3D"Beijing">Beijing</a>, and was asked by human rights activists=
 and groups to drop its sponsorship in March 2021 as part of diplomatic and=
 activist <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boycott" title=3D"Boycot=
t">boycotts</a> over alleged <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human=
_rights" title=3D"Human rights">human rights</a> violations by the <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_Communist_Party" title=3D"Chinese=
 Communist Party">Chinese Communist Party</a>, in particular the <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persecution_of_Uyghurs_in_China" title=3D"Pe=
rsecution of Uyghurs in China">persecution of Uyghurs in China</a>. These r=
equests were ignored by the company.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-198" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-198"><span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>198<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a>=
</sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-199" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-199"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>199<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-200"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_n=
ote-200"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>200<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-201" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-201"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>201<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Length_of_terms_of_service_=
agreements">Length of terms of service agreements</h3><span class=3D"mw-edi=
tsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAirbnb&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=
=3D19" title=3D"Edit section: Length of terms of service agreements"><span>=
edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In 2014, linguist <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mark_Liberman=
" title=3D"Mark Liberman">Mark Liberman</a> criticized the extreme length o=
f the legal agreements that Airbnb members are required to accept, with the=
 site's <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terms_of_service" title=3D=
"Terms of service">terms of service</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Privacy_policy" title=3D"Privacy policy">privacy policy</a>, and oth=
er policies amounting to "55081 words, or about the size of a short novel, =
though much less readable".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-202" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-202"><span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">[</span>202<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Legal_issues">Legal issues<=
/h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAirbnb&amp;a=
ction=3Dedit&amp;section=3D20" title=3D"Edit section: Legal issues"><span>e=
dit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Illegal_behavior_by_hosts">=
Illegal behavior by hosts</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D=
"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/inde=
x.php?title=3DAirbnb&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D21" title=3D"Edit sect=
ion: Illegal behavior by hosts"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-edit=
section-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Hosts have been accused of circumventing tax regulations,<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-203" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airb=
nb#cite_note-203"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>203<span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">]</span></a></sup> circumventing Airbnb's background checks and=
 subjecting guests to last-minute cancellations, moldy or rodent-infested l=
odging, theft, invasion of privacy, and even rape and murder,<sup id=3D"cit=
e_ref-204" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air=
bnb#cite_note-204"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>204<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-205" class=3D"reference"=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-205"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>205<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
><sup id=3D"cite_ref-206" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-206"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>206<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-207" clas=
s=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-2=
07"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>207<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup> as well as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bait-a=
nd-switch" title=3D"Bait-and-switch">bait-and-switch</a> scams in which the=
 guest does not receive the promised accommodation.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-208"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_n=
ote-208"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>208<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-209" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-209"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>209<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Airbnb=
 has noted that the number of these incidents is not statistically signific=
ant and has banned violators and associated accounts.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-21=
0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite=
_note-210"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>210<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In July 2024, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CNN" title=3D=
"CNN">CNN</a> noted that Airbnb includes significant disclaimers on some of=
 its policies, such as notifying users that its background checks should no=
t be relied on to identify "all past criminal convictions or <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sex_offender" title=3D"Sex offender">sex offende=
r</a> registrations =E2=80=A6 or other red flags" and that convictions for =
"murder, terrorism, rape or child molestation" are not automatic disqualifi=
ers for a host.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:1_211-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-:1-211"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>211<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Hidden_cameras">Hidden came=
ras</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracke=
t">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAirbnb&a=
mp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D22" title=3D"Edit section: Hidden cameras"><=
span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span><=
/div>
<p>There have been incidents of hosts secretly recording their guests using=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hidden_cameras" class=3D"mw-redir=
ect" title=3D"Hidden cameras">hidden cameras</a>, including in areas such a=
s bedrooms and bathrooms.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-212" class=3D"reference"><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-212"><span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">[</span>212<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-:0_213-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-:0-213"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>21=
3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-214" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note=
-214"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>214<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup> Publications such as <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/The_Washington_Post" title=3D"The Washington Post">The Washington =
Post</a></i><sup id=3D"cite_ref-215" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-215"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[=
</span>215<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and <i><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fast_Company" title=3D"Fast Company">Fast Co=
mpany</a><sup id=3D"cite_ref-216" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-216"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</s=
pan>216<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></i> have published g=
uides on how to find hidden cameras in an Airbnb rental.<sup id=3D"cite_ref=
-:0_213-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air=
bnb#cite_note-:0-213"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>213<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In a 2023 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Deposition_(law)" title=3D"Deposition (law)">deposition</a>, a=
n Airbnb employee testified that the company does not notify law enforcemen=
t as a matter of practice when a complaint of a hidden camera is raised, bu=
t may contact hosts about complaints for its internal inquiries. Law enforc=
ement experts said the company's practice could hinder criminal investigati=
ons due to suspects having time to destroy evidence.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:1_=
211-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#=
cite_note-:1-211"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>211<span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In March 2024, Airbnb announced a ban on indoor cameras for properti=
es listed on the site, scheduled to take effect on April 30. The changes al=
so involve a requirement for hosts to disclose the use of noise-decibel mon=
itoring equipment.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-217" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-217"><span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">[</span>217<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-:0_213-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Airbnb#cite_note-:0-213"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>213<span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> A <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/CNN" title=3D"CNN">CNN</a> investigation published in July 2024 f=
ound that Airbnb "consistently fails to protect its guests despite knowing =
hidden cameras are a persistent concern within its industry" and that the s=
trategies it relies on "have been aimed at preventing regulation of the sho=
rt-term rental market to allow the company to distance itself from responsi=
bility for guest safety and privacy."<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:1_211-2" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-:1-21=
1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>211<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Failure_to_provide_required=
_information_to_governments">Failure to provide required information to gov=
ernments</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-b=
racket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAir=
bnb&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D23" title=3D"Edit section: Failure to p=
rovide required information to governments"><span>edit</span></a><span clas=
s=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Many governments have passed laws requiring that Airbnb provide guest in=
formation so that local regulations can be enforced and <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel_tax" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Hotel tax">=
hotel taxes</a> are collected. Airbnb contested one such law in New York.<s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-218" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-218"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>218<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-219" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-21=
9"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>219<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup> However, in May 2019, Airbnb agreed to turn over some anony=
mized information for approximately 17,000 listings so that the city could =
pursue illegal rentals.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-220" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-220"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>220<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Simila=
r cases were settled in Boston and Miami.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-221" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-221"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>221<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup>
</p><p>Airbnb refused to provide required information to the Belgian govern=
ment, claiming the obligation to provide the information was not compatible=
 with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Union" title=3D"Eur=
opean Union">European Union</a> law. The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Constitutional_Court_(Belgium)" title=3D"Constitutional Court (Belgi=
um)">Belgian Constitutional Court</a> referred the dispute to the <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Court_of_Justice" title=3D"Europ=
ean Court of Justice">European Court of Justice</a>, which in April 2022 ru=
led that the requirement to transmit to tax authorities certain particulars=
 of tourist transactions was not contrary to European Union law and referre=
d the case back to the Belgian Constitutional Court.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-222=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_=
note-222"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>222<span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Legality_of_service_fees_in=
_the_Netherlands">Legality of service fees in the Netherlands</h3><span cla=
ss=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAirbnb&amp;action=3Dedit&=
amp;section=3D24" title=3D"Edit section: Legality of service fees in the Ne=
therlands"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</s=
pan></span></div>
<p>In March 2020, a subdistrict court ruling in the Netherlands found that =
Airbnb charging service fees to both the host and the guest was illegal and=
 that the 30,000 people who had rented as guests have a right for reimburse=
ment if they file claims. Airbnb filed countersuits in an attempt to gain c=
larity on the ruling.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-223" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbnb#cite_note-223"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>223<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
